pr_title: Querying the API directly without using the Neon Utilities
pr_body:
This PR adds functions for retrieving the NEON VST Data without using the neon-utilities R package as described in the issue https://github.com/weecology/neonVegWrangleR/issues/7 
It will add the following functions:

- [x] loadbyproduct
- [x] zipsbyproduct
- [x] stackbytable

pr_body:
@MarconiS, I have added checks for multiple site entries. Now we can download dataset for multiple sites and also stacks them at an instance. for e.g. 
```
path = zips_by_product('DP1.10098.001', site=['DELA','ABBY'], start_date='', end_date='')
stackedfiles = stackdatafiles(path, path, 'DP1.10098.001')
```
can you pls test this in your system.
